ods, and the broad geographical scope reflects the main focus of archaeological work in the Islamic world to the present day.Key FeaturesIncludes short case studies to allow the reader to examine the ways in which archaeologists collect and interpret material in specific contextsConsiders archaeological work conducted in the area stretching from Afghanistan and the Central Asian republics in the east to Spain in the westDraws comparisons with Islamic regions of sub-Saharan Africa and the Indian subcontinentIncludes a Glossary of archaeological terminology and Arabic, Persian and Turkish terms  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aExcavations (Archaeology)zIslamic countries. 0aIslamic antiquities. 0aIslamic civilization. 4aIslamic Studies. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z97831107804680 cprintz978074862310540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748629954?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748629954423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748629954/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK